div.p: Pragtudgave af Koranen i rigt dekoreret lakbind sandsynligvis udført i Persien.
Teksten er skrevet i Naskhī skriften, mens marginalnoterne er på persisk i Ta'līq skriften.
Kopieret af Rašīd al-Dīn i 1291 H [1874].

Beskrevet i: Catalogue of Arabic Manuscripts. Codices Arabici Additamenta and Codices Simonseniani Arabici by Ali Abd Alhussein Alhaidary and Stig T. Rasmussen. Copenhagen 1995, s. 38 (på arabisk 121).
A manificent Koran in a rich decorated lacquer binding probably made in Persia.
Text in Naskhī script, marginal notes in Persian in Ta'līq script.
Scribe: Rašīd al-Dīn. Copying date 1291 H [1874 CE].

Described in: Catalogue of Arabic Manuscripts. Codices Arabici Additamenta and Codices Simonseniani Arabici by Ali Abd Alhussein Alhaidary and Stig T. Rasmussen. Copenhagen 1995, p. 38 (in arabic p. 121).
